# Post-merge: checkout master and pull

After completing a merge of a branch into `master` (or when the user confirms a PR was merged on GitHub), run in this repo:

1. `git checkout master`
2. `git pull origin master` (after `git fetch` if needed)

Do this so the local workspace matches `origin/master` before further work.
